```dockerfile
# Stage 1: Chef - prepare Rust dependencies
FROM rust:1.78 AS chef
RUN cargo install cargo-chef
WORKDIR /app

# Stage 2: Rust Builder - build Rust binary
FROM chef AS rust-builder
COPY Cargo.toml Cargo.lock ./
RUN cargo chef prepare --recipe-path recipe.json
RUN cargo chef cook --release --recipe-path recipe.json
COPY server ./server
RUN cargo build --release --bin inference-server

# Stage 3: Python Builder - install ML dependencies
FROM python:3.11-slim-bookworm AS python-builder
RUN python -m venv /opt/venv
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"
RUN pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel && \
    pip install --no-cache-dir \
    torch==2.1.1 \
    transformers==4.36.2 \
    tokenizers==0.14.1 \
    safetensors==0.4.1

# Stage 4: Runtime - minimal final image
FROM debian:bookworm-slim
LABEL maintainer="ML Inference Team" \
      description="Rust + Python ML Inference Server" \
      version="1.0.0"

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    ca-certificates \
    curl \
    libssl3 \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

RUN groupadd -g 1000 inference && \
    useradd -u 1000 -g inference -s /sbin/nologin -c "Inference service user" inference

COPY --from=rust-builder /app/target/release/inference-server /usr/local/bin/inference-server
COPY --from=python-builder /opt/venv /opt/venv

RUN chmod +x /usr/local/bin/inference-server && \
    chown -R inference:inference /usr/local/bin/inference-server /opt/venv

USER inference
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH" \
    PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1

EXPOSE 8080

HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \
    CMD curl -f http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1

ENTRYPOINT ["/usr/local/bin/inference-server"]
CMD ["--port", "8080"]
